1
00:00:00,098 --> 00:00:08,611
Now as a daily practice, some like to start with a little ritual, bowing, lighting a candle and incense, and taking the refuges and training rules.

2
00:00:09,932 --> 00:00:13,657
Although this is not necessary, some small ceremony can set the tone.

3
00:00:15,101 --> 00:00:25,556
I have recorded the chant for bowing, taking the three refuges, in the Buddha Dhamma Sangha, and also the five training rules, should you want to take them before a sitting.

4
00:00:26,978 --> 00:00:29,262
There is also at the end a final bow.

5
00:00:30,288 --> 00:00:33,491
This is how to pronounce the Pali, the language of the scriptures.

6
00:00:34,853 --> 00:00:49,753
When bowing, The end of the word is like our Ang in I rang the bell.

7
00:00:51,415 --> 00:00:54,759
It means I bow to the Buddha, the Dharma and the Sangha.

8
00:00:56,393 --> 00:01:23,700
Boddhang Saranang Gacchami Dhammang Saranang Gacchami Sanggang Saranang Gacchami Duthi Ampi Boddhang Saranang Gacchami Duthi Ampi Dhammang Saranang Gacchami Duthi Ampi Sanggang Saranang Gacchami

9
00:01:25,468 --> 00:01:44,954
I take refuge in the Buddha, the Dhamma and the Sangha.

10
00:01:45,295 --> 00:01:49,381
For the second time, I take refuge in the Buddha, Dhamma, Sangha.

11
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:54,227
And for the third time, I take refuge in the Buddha, Dhamma and Sangha.

12
00:01:56,435 --> 00:01:59,659
The five training rules or precepts are pronounced like this.

13
00:02:00,822 --> 00:02:21,497
PANATI PATA VERAMANI SIKAPADANG SAMADI YAMI ADINADHANA VERAMANI SIKAPADANG SAMADI YAMI KAMESUMI CHACARA VERAMANI SIKAPADANG SAMADI YAMI

14
00:02:22,996 --> 00:02:40,951
And they are translated like this.

15
00:02:43,093 --> 00:02:51,501
Not to harm any living beings, not to take what is not freely given, not to abuse our sexual powers,

16
00:02:53,270 --> 00:02:59,337
not to use wrong speech, not to take any drugs or drinks that tend to cloud the mind.

17
00:02:59,358 --> 00:03:08,468
At the end of the session, it is customary to complete it with another three bows.

18
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:19,782
imāyā dhamānū dhammapattipatiya buddhāṃ puje mi dhammāṃ puje mi saṅgāṃ puje mi

19
00:03:21,062 --> 00:03:27,317
by following the path of the Dharma, the true law, I bow to the Buddha, the Dharma and the Sangha.

20
00:03:29,241 --> 00:03:36,979
And finally, before you rise, make a determination to devote this day, just this one day, to mindfulness with a caring heart.

